JD 10:

Your responsibilities:

-For assigned suppliers(TIER 2), identify global and local business needs, specifications and requirements as input for sourcing projects, category strategy and ongoing management of supplier relationships 
-Share knowledge with Category Manager  to develop and execute overarching forward looking global category strategy for suppliers (TIER2) in your scope 
-Collaborate with global business partners to understand strategic priorities, align on sub(category) strategy and ensure adherence to the ING Procurement Policy 
-Lead end to end global e-sourcing initiatives (RFI, RFQ/RFP, e-auctions) including gathering global requirements, market research, evaluate proposal, decision process (TCO analysis, scenario analysis, etc), conduct negotiation and awarding 
-Manage third-party risk securing compliance with regulation and ING Policy and standards 
-Perform supplier relationship management, performance management, issue management and resolution while facilitating supplier review and continuous improvement 
-Support Category Management with negotiations, selecting preferred suppliers and establishing buying channels within assigned scope. 
-Play a role as strategic contributor in fields like ESG, procurement best in class practice, cost savings initiatives 

