JD 14:

Key Responsibilities:

Lead strategic supplier management, including risk, performance, relationship, value delivery, and supplier development.
Guide global category teams in developing, communicating, and approving sourcing strategies that reflect regional requirements and market conditions and coordinating handoff to regional teams for supplier selection and implementation.
Plan, negotiate, and contract with suppliers, ensuring agreements meet BD’s global needs—from small to large ($100M) service agreements.
Develop best in class multi-year roadmaps for savings, value creation, and innovation opportunities based on market intel and business needs
Monitor internal customer and supply market changes impacting sourcing strategy.
Lead supplier selection, RFX development, proposal evaluation, and stakeholder approval, ensuring effective communication of supply base.
Execute supplier relationship management for key suppliers and oversee global supplier activities.
Apply source-to-pay processes, including customer-centric support and preferred payment methods.
Maintain stakeholder relationships globally.
Develop and maintain risk mitigation plans and ensure supply base compliance with corporate procedures and legal requirements.
Drive global category team effectiveness mentor regional sourcing associates as needed
Drive budget favorability by proactively identifying budget gaps and engaging stakeholders through strategic communications and consensus, resulting in cost savings and value opportunities.

